if there’s one takeaway I learned performing my 2nd umrah Alhamdulillah…is that as much as I need Allah during my difficult times, I also desperately need Allah during my happy times. 

I came back from this trip not wanting more or asking for more but just being content with the day to day. Waking up just…grateful. 

I think it comes with age…this new found spirituality & I’m just happy to be here in these moments continuing to work on my spirituality with no perfect rhyme or routine. 

Just a human being trying everyday. ❤️
Clearly where I left my heart 🥹❤️ 🕋 #missingit
Thanking Allah for the opportunity to visit 😭 missing it everyday 🤲🏼 🕋
Thank you Allah, that is all 🤲🏼💕

wishing you all more peace, love, health & spirituality in 2023 🤲🏼 more kindness, more smiles, more giving, more healing & more gratitude Alhamdulillah ❤️ 

#2023 #spirituality #gratitude #alhamdulillah #mashAllah #Allahisgreater #newyear

May Allah continue to help me as a mother learn the wisdom of guiding you Zayd on the straight path & continue to learn to love Allah (swt) & our Prophet (ﷺ) 

Out of all the opportunities for accomplishment in this dunya, i hope that Allah will always be at the forefront of everything you do zayd. 

❤️ happy 10th #mashAllah

🫖 8 cardamoms 
🫖 4 cloves 
🫖 5 tsp of Al-Kbous Yemeni tea 
🫖 4.5 cups of water 
🫖 1 cup of evaporated milk

-Crush cardamom + cloves & add them in teapot.
-Add loose tea 
-Add water & bring to boil 
-Boil tea on low-medium for 5-7 minutes 
-Add carnation milk & bring to boil 
-Let it boil on low for 7-10 minutes 
-Add desired sugar
